name: Sweet Gravel Necklace
description:
Ingots of sterling silver dangle lightly on golden rings. These ingots are made by melting each piece of silver on a block of charcoal and manipulating each one individually while still molten. They are then drilled and oxidized, and finally polished so that the deep grooves and crevices are visible.  Each necklace is individually crafted, so expect yours to be one-of-a-kind.

MATERIALS
Sterling silver on 14k gold fill chain

MEASUREMENTS
Pendant appx 2"
24" chain

COLLECTION
Meta

Meta is the Greek preposition meaning ‘after’, ‘beyond’, ‘adjacent’, ‘self’.  The works in this collection are little studies in transformation, the power of change.  Life is never clean and perfect, we but in our imperfections and flaws there is beauty.  A real beauty that is founded in truth, not myth.  Many of the shapes and forms in this collection are random, one-of-a-kind, deeply textured, and require moving the metal through multiple stages.  Meta is about honoring where we’ve been and the real work that we do to change and grow.

name: The Mitsuro Solitaire // Yellow Gold
description:
DESCRIPTION 
Mitsuro is an ancient Japanese wax made of beeswax and pine resin, this band was formed around a mandrel and has a 'hikime' texture which mimics bamboo. This technique dates back to 760 AD and only a handful of American and Japanese artists are keeping the art alive today. The delicate processes reward is in the highly textured designs that feel plant-like.

Mitsuro is an ancient Japanese wax made of beeswax and pine resin, this band was formed around a mandrel and has a 'hikime' texture which mimics bamboo. This technique dates back to 760 AD and only a handful of American and Japanese artists are keeping the art alive today. The delicate processes reward is in the highly textured designs that feel plant-like.
